{
    "id": "colliderutil",
    "lang": "en-us",
    "name": "ColliderUtil",
    "description": "Give an object a physical shape so it can bump into, stand on, or detect other objects — boxes, capsules, spheres, meshes, and wheels.",
    "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/colliderutil",
    "tags": [
        "uniscript",
        "colliderutil",
        "collider",
        "collision",
        "physics"
    ],
    "previous": {
        "name": "DictionaryUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/dictionaryutil"
    },
    "next": {
        "name": "PhysicsUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/physicsutil"
    },
    "content": [
        {
            "id": "block-001",
            "tag": "h1",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "ColliderUtil"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-002",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "A **collider** is an object's physical shape — the invisible boundary that lets it bump into walls, stand on floors, or notice when something touches it. `ColliderUtil` adds a collider to an object and lets you control which objects it ignores."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-003",
            "tag": "note",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Most objects you place from the editor already come with a collider. You only need `ColliderUtil` when you build or change an object from script and want to give it a shape."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-004",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Choosing a shape"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-005",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Pick the shape that best matches the object. Simpler shapes (box, capsule, sphere) are faster and smoother than a mesh collider, so prefer them when you can."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-006",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "Best for"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`AddBoxCollider(this)`", "Crates, walls, platforms, and most blocky objects."],
                ["`AddCapsuleCollider(this)`", "Characters and rounded, upright objects — slides nicely along surfaces."],
                ["`AddSphereCollider(this)`", "Balls, coins, and round pickups."],
                ["`AddMeshCollider(this)`", "Complex shapes that need exact contours (use sparingly — it's heavier)."],
                ["`AddWheelCollider(this)`", "Vehicle wheels, for driving physics."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-007",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "class Coin",
                "{",
                "    void OnInit()",
                "    {",
                "        // Give this coin a round shape so the player can collect it.",
                "        ColliderUtil.AddSphereCollider(this);",
                "    }",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-008",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Letting objects pass through each other"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-009",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`SetIgnoreCollisions` tells an object to stop colliding with every object that has one of the given tags. This is handy when, say, you don't want bullets from the same team to hit each other."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-010",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Build a list of tags to ignore.",
                "List ignoreTags = ListUtil.New();",
                "ListUtil.Add(ignoreTags, \"teammate\");",
                "",
                "// Stop colliding with anything tagged \"teammate\".",
                "ColliderUtil.SetIgnoreCollisions(this, ignoreTags, true);",
                "",
                "// Pass 'false' later to start colliding again.",
                "ColliderUtil.SetIgnoreCollisions(this, ignoreTags, false);"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-011",
            "tag": "important",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "A playable **character** already manages its own shape. Don't add a separate collider to a Character object — it can fight with the one the character already has. See [CharacterUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-us/characterutil)."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-012",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Full method reference"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-013",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Returns",
                "Method",
                "Parameters"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`void`", "`AddBoxCollider`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`AddCapsuleCollider`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`AddSphereCollider`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`AddMeshCollider`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`AddWheelCollider`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetIgnoreCollisions`", "`uniscript, List tags, bool ignoreCollision`"]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-014",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "A collider gives an object a shape; to make it actually move, bounce, or fall you also need physics. See [PhysicsUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-us/physicsutil)."
        }
    ]
}
